I have survived so many deadly things, I have fought for the right to live a free life like everyone else - and I am in the process of rebuilding it. I can finally be myself, fully and completely.

It's not easy now, this life was not made for me. It goes from match to match, never a break. But then I'm one who does not stop either, no matter how much it annoys me sometimes!

This is new, fresh and unfamiliar; but damn I have managed so much heaven!

This life is new to me. It's just over two years since I got out of violence and a life with things I should not have had. Also good, wonderful things, but always something else behind. I take it with me as I learn to navigate the world as free.

I have managed so much more than I thought I could, because I have always been told something else. I'm vulnerable, I shut myself in as a defense when things get too much with people; but I'm still trying.
